document.text: SERGIO A. CARRILLO AND ALBERTO LASTRA
The aim of this work is to establish the existence, uniqueness and
Gevrey character of formal power series solutions of
doubly-singular equations. Using a new family of Nagumo norms adapted for
-differences we find new types of optimal divergence associated with these
problems. We also provide some examples to illustrate our results.
